TopicTitle: ETT / Unmanned before manned always gives me command pod

Articles.Content:
Hello,

I am trying to run KSP with the more "realistic" tech trees. Have tried Unmanned before manned, and ETT, but both of them still give me the command pod mk1 as starting pod, and not one of the unmanned ones.

I checked the CFG files in both mods, and UBM should give me probecoreocto at start, and ETT should give me probeCoreSphere. But they don't and i do not understand why... I don't even have parachutes yet, so i can't do ANYTHING with the new tech tree. 

What is causing this?

Also, as side question, is Kerbalism working with one of these? 

Just to confirm: Tested it with a fresh KSP install and it is the same. I have the command pod, not one of the unmanned probes
